    "excerpt": "This prayer by Rabbi Alfred Gottschalk at the second inauguration of President Ronald Reagan was recorded in the United States’ <a href=\"https://archive.org/stream/congressionalrec131aunit#page/n319/mode/2up\">Congressional Record on January 21, 1985</a>. . . .",
    "content": "<table style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" class=\"draggable toggleable-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th id=\"x\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><a href=\"/translate/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Contribute a translation</a></th>\n<th style=\"text-align: left;\">Source (English)</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\">\nWe the people turn to You, O God, in prayer.<br />\nWe have come again to this place which stirs our hearts<br />\nto reaffirm the highest ideals of our Nation.<br />\nThe sacred oaths about to be pronounced in Your name<br />\nreflect the awesome responsibilities entrusted<br />\nto our President and Vice President<br />\nby the American people.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\">\nMay You, who are the rock of ages,<br />\nguide them in protecting<br />\nthe Constitution of our beloved Commonwealth,<br />\nfounded in faith,<br />\nwhich ensures unity without uniformity.<br />\nSustain them, O God,<br />\nas they advance the American way<br />\nwhich &#8220;gives to bigotry no sanction&#8221;<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_1');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> From George Washington&#8217;s &#8220;<a href=\"/?p=22602\">Letter to the Jews of Newport</a>,&#8221; August 17th, 1790.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_1', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\nto &#8220;malevolence no hope.&#8221;<span class=\"footnote_referrer\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" onkeypress=\"footnote_moveToReference__1('footnote_plugin_reference__1_2');\" ><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]</sup></a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip\"> Ibid, but with creative liberty.&nbsp;</span></span><script type=\"text/javascript\"> jQuery('#footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2').tooltip({ tip: '#footnote_plugin_tooltip_text__1_2', tipClass: 'footnote_tooltip', effect: 'fade', predelay: 0, fadeInSpeed: 200, delay: 400, fadeOutSpeed: 200, position: 'center right', relative: true, offset: [0, 0], });</script>&nbsp;\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\">\nO source of all life,<br />\nenshrine in their hearts the knowledge<br />\nthat all are created in Your image<br />\nand that life —<br />\nYour gift to us —<br />\nis sacred.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\">\nInspire our leaders<br />\nto defeat hunger and hurt,<br />\nto promote compassion<br />\nand to find successful ways<br />\nto assure the weak their share of America&#8217;s promise.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\">\nIn humility,<br />\nwe pray that this opportunity for renewal<br />\nwill advance reconciliation in the family of nations,<br />\nguaranteeing peace in our world and tranquility<br />\nin the farthest reaches of our universe.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\">\nMay those who follow us,<br />\nour children and our children&#8217;s children,<br />\nbless our President and Vice President,<br />\ntheir families,<br />\nand all those associated with them in Government,<br />\nand may all remember this time<br />\nand this administration<br />\nas that in which their future was made secure.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\">\nO God, may You, who makes peace in high places,<br />\nhelp us here on Earth to find the way to peace.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"liturgy\" lang=\"heb-Hebr\">\n<p></span></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"vertical-align:top;\">\n<div class=\"english\" lang=\"eng-Latn\">\nBlessed are You, O God.<br />\nAleichem Shalom, grantor of peace. <em>Amen</em>.\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<hr />\n<p>This prayer by Rabbi Alfred Gottschalk at the second inauguration of President Ronald Reagan was recorded in the United States’ <a href=\"https://archive.org/stream/congressionalrec131aunit#page/n319/mode/2up\">Congressional Record on January 21, 1985</a>.</p>\n<h3>Source(s)</h3>\n<p><span style=\"float: right;\"><div id=\"attachment_11294\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Inauguration-Day-Prayer-for-President-Ronald-Reagan-by-Rabbi-Alfred-Gottschalk-1985-1.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-11294\" src=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Inauguration-Day-Prayer-for-President-Ronald-Reagan-by-Rabbi-Alfred-Gottschalk-1985-1-300x235.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"235\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-11294\" srcset=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Inauguration-Day-Prayer-for-President-Ronald-Reagan-by-Rabbi-Alfred-Gottschalk-1985-1-300x235.png 300w, https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Inauguration-Day-Prayer-for-President-Ronald-Reagan-by-Rabbi-Alfred-Gottschalk-1985-1.png 386w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><p id=\"caption-attachment-11294\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Inauguration Day Prayer for President Ronald Reagan by Rabbi Alfred Gottschalk (1985) part 1</p></div></span> <span style=\"float: left;\"><div id=\"attachment_11295\" style=\"width: 197px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Inauguration-Day-Prayer-for-President-Ronald-Reagan-by-Rabbi-Alfred-Gottschalk-1985-2.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-11295\" src=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Inauguration-Day-Prayer-for-President-Ronald-Reagan-by-Rabbi-Alfred-Gottschalk-1985-2-187x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"187\" height=\"300\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-11295\" srcset=\"https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Inauguration-Day-Prayer-for-President-Ronald-Reagan-by-Rabbi-Alfred-Gottschalk-1985-2-187x300.png 187w, https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Inauguration-Day-Prayer-for-President-Ronald-Reagan-by-Rabbi-Alfred-Gottschalk-1985-2.png 387w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 187px) 100vw, 187px\" /></a><p id=\"caption-attachment-11295\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Inauguration Day Prayer for President Ronald Reagan by Rabbi Alfred Gottschalk (1985) part 2</p></div></span><span class=\"\" style=\"display:block;clear:both;height: 0px;border-top-width:0px;border-bottom-width:0px;\"></span></p>\n<div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\">Notes</span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" style=\"display: none;; display: none;\" onclick=\"footnote_expand_collapse_reference_container__1();\"></span></p></div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container__1\" style=\"\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">Notes</caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_1');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >1</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">From George Washington&#8217;s &#8220;<a href=\"/?p=22602\">Letter to the Jews of Newport</a>,&#8221; August 17th, 1790.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" id=\"footnote_plugin_reference__1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index pointer\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor__1('footnote_plugin_tooltip__1_2');\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" class=\"footnote_plugin_link\" >2</a></th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\">Ibid, but with creative liberty.</td></tr>\r\n\r\n </tbody> </table> </div></div><script type=\"text/javascript\"> function footnote_expand_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').show(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_container_collapse_button__1').text('−'); } function footnote_collapse_reference_container__1() { jQuery('#footnote_references_container__1').hide(); jQuery('#footnote_reference_c